profile:
{"first_name": "Tom", "last_name": "Forsberg", "full_name": "Tom Forsberg", "headline": "Chief Revenue Officer at Big Think Capital", "title": "Chief Revenue Officer", "picture": {"source": "https://images.ai-ark.com/LMhVSxBvU5EIrkht72n1ODZIbM8TZHDL3duoh6hAcr8/exp:1780358399/rs:fill:80:80/plain/s3://ark-person/images/2c8e7e1b-e52e-85c0-8887-4d72155232bb.jpg"}, "background": {"source": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5616AQFdWHu63i3Yqw/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/0/1587402625167?e=1778716800&v=beta&t=PF-JpclT0IjmxxnhVHBL1dk3oFTMkTE2dB6TGWsoFKI"}, "birth_date": null, "summary": "Tom Forsberg is the Chief Revenue Officer at Big Think Capital and is primarily responsible for driving all of the Company’s revenue streams including it’s syndication investment platform. Tom is a seasoned and accomplished industry veteran and is accountable for driving revenue growth, by leveraging and aligning all revenue generating departments. Tom has been with Big Think Capital since inception and has been an instrumental part of it’s success and growth. Prior to joining Big Think Capital, Tom was a Sales Manager at a national telecommunications Company where he regularly achieved President’s Club status.

Tom is a graduate of Bryant University with a Bachelor’s degree in Finance. Tom is a Division-1 Captain, All American athlete and attended Bryant University on a full Lacrosse scholarship. Tom takes a Client centric approach to business and will go to great lengths to understand the vision of the Company and then execute accordingly. Tom is not afraid of a challenge and prides himself on his ability to earn his Client’s trust and long-term retention.

In his spare time, Tom still enjoys working but will occasionally find time to wakeboard, snowboard or spend time with family."}

{"first_name": "Ethan", "last_name": "Zolga", "full_name": "Ethan Zolga", "headline": "Vice President – Specialty Finance | Multi-Market Expansion (Miami & LA)", "title": "Vice President - Specialty Finance", "picture": {"source": "https://images.ai-ark.com/qAcn7REOfgTXwZ6-teRB2p7qfj8aMlxCF8H457B5Yts/exp:1780358399/rs:fill:80:80/plain/s3://ark-person/images/149a08ee-5b99-8a43-edad-6003fded89dc.jpg"}, "background": {"source": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E16AQHkQdLuYBpodg/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/B4EZ0HixeSI8Ag-/0/1773948049636?e=1778716800&v=beta&t=YBMZioZbRbeUoi2S8tL4WXM8IIwAdvFGIdagA-Dr51Y"}, "birth_date": null, "summary": "Ethan is a member of Big Think Capital’s senior leadership team, leading the firm’s Specialty Finance Division and overseeing operations across the Miami and Los Angeles offices - both of which he played a foundational role in launching and scaling.

He is responsible for hiring, team development, revenue performance, and direct deal oversight within these markets, while driving expansion across SBA, Equipment Finance, Residential & Commercial Real Estate, and other emerging specialty verticals.

Beyond divisional leadership, Ethan contributes to broader company growth strategy. Identifying new product opportunities, structuring strategic partnerships, and aligning expansion efforts with long-term organizational vision."}

{"first_name": "Salvatore", "last_name": "Vitale", "full_name": "Salvatore Vitale", "headline": "CSO @ Big Think Capital", "title": "Chief Strategy Officer", "picture": {"source": "https://images.ai-ark.com/LTZnpDOxG4wGq7G_AuzRooyQPB_U1PVvZQH3NtfunUQ/exp:1780358399/rs:fill:80:80/plain/s3://ark-person/images/04f1c711-ca3b-086d-ab43-860e76b3476d.jpg"}, "background": {"source": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E16AQGZEGaP3omd9g/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/B4EZ0MJgFUIkAY-/0/1774025310899?e=1778716800&v=beta&t=O3iX2Ap7290oqZG1t_u2YzwMXxDsQEfMIXVI2QfyhIY"}, "birth_date": "1600-02-19", "summary": "Sal is the Chief Strategy Officer and is responsible for new business ventures and strategic initiatives. Sal is a strategic change agent and transformative leader within the company. He is a Long Island native who received his B.A. in Finance from Marquette University. Sal began his career in the financial sector and became a top-performing consultant in the Wealth Management field at a Fortune 500 company. After recognizing his desire to combine his skill and entrepreneurial spirit, he made the transition to alternative lending.

His role is to lead the creation of long-term value for the firm from customers, markets, and relationships. Sal's expertise within the industry helps accelerate sales and profitability by developing and implementing innovative operational and growth strategies. He is known for implementing operating efficiencies and developing high-performance teams within the company.  

Sal’s main focus is to drive all strategic deal-making efforts to improve and broaden the scope of Big Think Capital’s partnership offerings. He aims to build strategies and product channels that will enhance the company’s long-term value proposition to both our clients and partners."}

{"first_name": "Robert", "last_name": "Serritella", "full_name": "Robert Serritella", "headline": "Director, Data Analytics at Big Think Capital", "title": "Director, Data Analytics", "picture": {"source": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQHH0592Htcx_w/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1719252634032?e=1778716800&v=beta&t=ZJhBDSv3crNGl-j9EC2M_MZbzc0_FH4n7cI9oDG6qiQ"}, "background": {"source": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E16AQGyYFXZAcJwQw/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/B4EZl3.qIFKkAY-/0/1758654538707?e=1778716800&v=beta&t=r2DwdBvTg1v3bDcjmGlr2j1TJ-p2dc2v99wMWvww2rI"}, "birth_date": null, "summary": "Welcome to my LinkedIn profile! I am the Director of Data Analytics at Big Think Capital, a comprehensive financial network and marketplace. My goal is to help uncover new ways to match our clients with the services which best fit their business needs.

My industry experience began while working with one of Long Island's leading fintech CRM providers. This multi-faceted role provided the gateway to not only learning the software side of the space, but also examining which practices work best for businesses and their clients. It was during this time that that I first interfaced with Big Think Capital and collaborated with its leaders to devise customized solutions which would best serve their network.

I earned my Bachelor of Science in Computer Science from Villanova University. While attending, I served as Co-President of the school's chapter of the Association for Computing Machinery, and dedicated time as a Volunteer Peer Tutoring Coordinator. I was also part of one of the first student-led teams to utilize Villanova's virtual Reality CAVE, which garnered award-recognition and a shared spotlight on CBS News Philadelphia."}
